Some people tell me that the coconut emoji can be considered slightly racist since some say it's you're one race on the outside but another on the inside. Does anyone know about this? I never heard of this but I also don't use a lot of emojis because I just never did.

Someone- who is French and not on social media a lot said that to me but when I explained the CONTEXT (remember- we all exist in the context , etc) and where it originated- from her speech- they totally understood. I suggest using the coconut and the palm tree together to avoid confusion...
